---
import BaseHead from '../components/BaseHead.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import { SITE_DESCRIPTION, SITE_TITLE } from '../consts';
---

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
	<head>
		<BaseHead title={SITE_TITLE} description={SITE_DESCRIPTION} />
	</head>
	<body>
		<Header />

		<main>
			<hero-section>
				<h2>Can We Build It? Yes We Can! 🏗️</h2>
				<p>Welcome to Bob's construction headquarters! Here you'll find building tips, project updates, and all the wisdom you need to tackle any construction challenge.</p>
			</hero-section>

			<construction-motto>
				"Measure twice, cut once, and always wear your safety gear!" 
				<span class="tools">🔨</span>
				<span class="tools">🪚</span>
				<span class="tools">🔧</span>
			</construction-motto>

			<section id="blog">
				<h2 style="color: var(--construction-orange); font-size: 2.2rem; text-align: center; margin-bottom: 2rem;">Latest from the Construction Site 📰</h2>
				
				<blog-grid>
					<blog-post>
						<h3>Building the Perfect Toolshed</h3>
						<time datetime="2024-07-25">July 25, 2024</time>
						<p>Every builder needs a proper toolshed! Today I'll walk you through the step-by-step process of constructing a durable, organized workspace that will keep your tools safe and accessible. From foundation to roof, we'll cover all the essential techniques.</p>
					</blog-post>

					<blog-post>
						<h3>Safety First: Essential PPE for Every Job</h3>
						<time datetime="2024-07-22">July 22, 2024</time>
						<p>Safety should never be an afterthought on any construction site. In this post, I'll cover the essential personal protective equipment every builder should have, from hard hats to steel-toed boots. Remember, we can fix it, but safety comes first!</p>
					</blog-post>

					<blog-post>
						<h3>Concrete Fundamentals: Mixing and Pouring</h3>
						<time datetime="2024-07-20">July 20, 2024</time>
						<p>A strong foundation starts with properly mixed concrete. Join me as I demonstrate the correct ratios, mixing techniques, and pouring methods that ensure your projects stand the test of time. Scoop and Muck would be proud!</p>
					</blog-post>

					<blog-post>
						<h3>Teamwork Makes the Dream Work</h3>
						<time datetime="2024-07-18">July 18, 2024</time>
						<p>No construction project is a one-person job! Learn how effective communication, task delegation, and team coordination can turn any challenging build into a smooth operation. Wendy always says teamwork is key!</p>
					</blog-post>
				</blog-grid>
			</section>

			<tool-tip>
				Always check your measurements three times before making any cuts. A small mistake early on can become a big problem later!
			</tool-tip>

			<project-showcase id="projects">
				<h2>Featured Construction Projects 🏗️</h2>
				<project-grid>
					<project-card>
						<span class="emoji">🏠</span>
						<h4>Sunflower Valley School</h4>
						<p>A complete renovation of the local school, featuring new classrooms, a modern playground, and energy-efficient systems.</p>
					</project-card>

					<project-card>
						<span class="emoji">🌉</span>
						<h4>Community Bridge Repair</h4>
						<p>Structural reinforcement and safety upgrades to the main bridge connecting our neighborhoods.</p>
					</project-card>

					<project-card>
						<span class="emoji">🏗️</span>
						<h4>Town Hall Expansion</h4>
						<p>Adding a new wing to accommodate the growing community needs while preserving historical architecture.</p>
					</project-card>

					<project-card>
						<span class="emoji">🚧</span>
						<h4>Road Construction Project</h4>
						<p>Paving new roads and improving infrastructure to support the town's development and traffic flow.</p>
					</project-card>
				</project-grid>
			</project-showcase>

			<tool-tip>
				When working with power tools, always ensure they're properly maintained and inspected before each use. A well-maintained tool is a safe tool!
			</tool-tip>

			<section id="tools" style="background: white; padding: 2rem; border-radius: 15px; box-shadow: 0 4px 8px rgba(0,0,0,0.1);">
				<h2 style="color: var(--safety-blue); text-align: center; margin-bottom: 1.5rem;">Essential Tools in Bob's Toolbox 🧰</h2>
				<p style="text-align: center; font-size: 1.1rem; color: #555;">From hammers to hard hats, every tool has its purpose. Here are the must-haves for any construction project:</p>
				
				<ul style="list-style: none; display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(200px, 1fr)); gap: 1rem; margin-top: 2rem; text-align: center;">
					<li style="padding: 1rem; background: var(--primary-yellow); border-radius: 10px;">🔨 Hammer</li>
					<li style="padding: 1rem; background: var(--primary-yellow); border-radius: 10px;">🪚 Saw</li>
					<li style="padding: 1rem; background: var(--primary-yellow); border-radius: 10px;">🔧 Wrench Set</li>
					<li style="padding: 1rem; background: var(--primary-yellow); border-radius: 10px;">📏 Measuring Tape</li>
					<li style="padding: 1rem; background: var(--primary-yellow); border-radius: 10px;">📐 Level</li>
					<li style="padding: 1rem; background: var(--primary-yellow); border-radius: 10px;">🪛 Screwdriver Set</li>
				</ul>
			</section>
		</main>
		<Footer/>
	</body>
</html>